1
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:06,751
I write this, so it can be remembered.

2
00:01:06,870 --> 00:01:11,030
But I don't know who will read it.

3
00:01:12,389 --> 00:01:15,150
Denmark was under the sun...

4
00:01:15,269 --> 00:01:19,429
and no one could,
in their wildest dreams, imagine...

5
00:01:19,548 --> 00:01:25,389
that the country would soon experience
its heaviest and most bloody defeat.

6
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:30,028
It is the story of a forgotten time
and a forgotten war.

7
00:01:30,147 --> 00:01:33,828
About Laust and Peter, Johan and Didrich...

8
00:01:33,947 --> 00:01:39,388
...Sofia and mother Karen Dinesen,
Einar, Erasmus and Alfred...

9
00:01:39,507 --> 00:01:41,707
...and the destiny of others...

10
00:01:41,826 --> 00:01:47,747
...who were victims of euphoric
folly of mad people.

11
00:01:48,786 --> 00:01:51,466
And our own faith in them.

12
00:01:53,425 --> 00:01:58,546
I am Inge.
I am a freight manager's daughter...

13
00:01:58,665 --> 00:02:02,625
...Laust's and Peter's love.

14
00:02:02,744 --> 00:02:06,105
I am the last living witness.

15
00:02:06,224 --> 00:02:10,104
I have the time, that disappeared.

16
00:02:18,902 --> 00:02:24,063
If we just gather over here,
before we move on to the history center.

17
00:02:25,382 --> 00:02:27,823
Okay. It was here...

18
00:02:27,942 --> 00:02:32,862
...April 18, 1864, the Danish army
fought against the Prussian supremacy.

19
00:02:32,981 --> 00:02:37,542
Karoline, hello.
Tap Karoline on the shoulder.

20
00:02:37,661 --> 00:02:40,181
Today, there is not much to see.

21
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:45,341
There are some grooves in the ground,
trays, and the hint of redoubts.

22
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:52,941
But imagine if you can...

23
00:02:53,060 --> 00:02:57,860
...that the Prussian army was over there...

24
00:02:57,979 --> 00:03:02,100
...and the Danish defense fortifications
were located in the countryside here.

25
00:03:02,219 --> 00:03:06,979
Is anybody listening?
Now we run all the way over there.

26
00:03:07,098 --> 00:03:10,019
Dybboel Mill.

27
00:03:13,377 --> 00:03:16,698
Young Danish soldiers struggled here...

28
00:03:16,817 --> 00:03:20,697
...in a completely impossible
and hopeless battle...

29
00:03:20,817 --> 00:03:24,258
...against a giant Prussian army.

30
00:03:27,456 --> 00:03:30,416
Dybboel Mill.

31
00:03:32,536 --> 00:03:37,016
These are the finest top leaves.
I have a pound.

32
00:03:37,135 --> 00:03:40,936
I will piss rich. Try it.

33
00:03:45,094 --> 00:03:48,655
You'll never get rich, Zlatko.

34
00:04:02,412 --> 00:04:09,773
On 18/04/1864, in redoubt, here fell
Kaptsur Lundbye...

35
00:04:09,892 --> 00:04:15,453
...of the 2nd Regt
and many of the rank and file...

36
00:04:15,572 --> 00:04:19,012
...whose names are not recorded.

37
00:04:19,131 --> 00:04:23,612
How stupid!
There is a monument because they fell.

38
00:04:24,971 --> 00:04:27,852
Oh, I fell. Give me a monument.

39
00:04:27,971 --> 00:04:30,771
Idiot!

40
00:05:31,684 --> 00:05:34,485
Good morning.

41
00:05:47,363 --> 00:05:52,604
Noah did, just as God had commanded him.

42
00:05:54,802 --> 00:06:02,003
Now, if there were two animals of
everything, there were also two lice?

43
00:06:02,121 --> 00:06:08,322
Noah took two of each.
All living creatures.

44
00:06:08,441 --> 00:06:12,522
- But what would you do with lice?
- All creatures are God's work.

45
00:06:12,641 --> 00:06:17,041
- But lice?!
- You are happy when you are "lice free".

46
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:21,441
So without lice
there would not be any "lice free".

47
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:29,320
- Damn!
- That's enough!

48
00:06:38,678 --> 00:06:41,958
- Are you coming, Peter?
- Come on.

49
00:06:48,357 --> 00:06:51,197
Peter.

50
00:06:55,877 --> 00:06:59,517
And so Denmark is at war.
And so they rally...

51
00:06:59,636 --> 00:07:04,157
...for no soldier is so brave
as the Danish soldier.

52
00:07:04,276 --> 00:07:10,637
The german is on the run,
and Schleswig would bend your neck.

53
00:07:10,755 --> 00:07:14,435
Yes, children.
Many of your fathers are down there...

54
00:07:14,555 --> 00:07:17,356
...and you should be proud...

55
00:07:17,475 --> 00:07:21,395
...that they defended Denmark
to the last drop of blood.

56
00:07:21,514 --> 00:07:26,795
Peter's father is also included. Isn't
that true, Peter, who chose to be late.

57
00:07:26,914 --> 00:07:31,354
The german is currently
eating Schleswig up like the wolf...

58
00:07:31,473 --> 00:07:36,834
...enticing the lost sheep.
Come on. Come with me.

59
00:07:36,953 --> 00:07:40,313
But no. For here is the Kingdom of Denmark.

60
00:07:40,432 --> 00:07:45,153
And it goes all the way down here.
So Schleswig is in the fold.

61
00:07:45,272 --> 00:07:49,233
They think that they are outside,
but we'll have to change that.

62
00:07:49,352 --> 00:07:52,952
- Yes, Einar.
- Isn't German Schleswig the most spoken language?

63
00:07:53,071 --> 00:07:56,351
Yes, but it must stop...

64
00:07:56,470 --> 00:08:00,391
because we do not have other languages
than Danish in Denmark...

65
00:08:00,511 --> 00:08:05,672
...and that's why God gave us the flag.

66
00:08:05,790 --> 00:08:08,870
- Did it really fall from the sky?
- Yes.

67
00:08:08,990 --> 00:08:13,111
The good God let the danish flag
with the white cross...

68
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:15,710
...drop down to us Danish...

69
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:19,829
because He loves us more
than all the others.

70
00:08:19,948 --> 00:08:22,869
- Hooray.
- Hooray.

71
00:08:22,989 --> 00:08:25,429
Are you sure?

72
00:08:25,548 --> 00:08:30,389
Yes, if you just do it long enough,
something will come out.

73
00:08:30,508 --> 00:08:36,108
I do it at least once a day
and bring it into the jar over there.

74
00:08:38,867 --> 00:08:41,507
Here it comes.

75
00:08:58,665 --> 00:09:00,905
See.

76
00:09:11,744 --> 00:09:15,064
It's what you do for children.

77
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:22,783
Damn, I can not. Damn.

78
00:09:22,903 --> 00:09:26,384
Don't worry. It will come.

79
00:09:27,703 --> 00:09:31,503
Why are they ringing so many times?

80
00:09:32,901 --> 00:09:34,782
It is Didrich.

81
00:09:34,902 --> 00:09:37,182
You are home.

82
00:09:37,301 --> 00:09:43,222
I was 12 years old in 1851,
when the soldiers returned home.

83
00:09:44,781 --> 00:09:49,341
They had defeated the Prussians
and the Schleswig rebels...

84
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:53,901
...and now the country was
overtaken with excitement.

85
00:10:01,899 --> 00:10:07,940
I still remember the women crying,
as they revisited their sons and men.

86
00:10:08,059 --> 00:10:11,779
I remember clearly
how brilliant Didrich looked...

87
00:10:11,898 --> 00:10:17,219
...when he rode on his
high horse and looked like a prince.

88
00:10:18,697 --> 00:10:24,338
How I ran barefoot along side
and looked admiringly at him...

89
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:29,057
...and the fine company,
who received him with enthusiasm.

90
00:10:29,176 --> 00:10:31,897
See my son. Look at him.

91
00:10:32,016 --> 00:10:34,416
There we have the hero.

92
00:10:34,536 --> 00:10:38,737
Hooray! Hooray! Hooray!

93
00:10:38,856 --> 00:10:41,456
Didrich.

94
00:10:47,655 --> 00:10:49,775
And... Yes, it's great.

95
00:10:49,895 --> 00:10:53,775
Come on. Cognac. Cognac for my son.

96
00:10:53,895 --> 00:10:56,935
Come on, boy.

97
00:10:58,134 --> 00:11:01,414
- Bang! Bang!
- Don't shoot me!

98
00:11:03,854 --> 00:11:07,294
- Satan's German!
- Bang!

99
00:11:23,211 --> 00:11:25,611
Mother?

100
00:11:34,731 --> 00:11:37,171
Father?

101
00:11:39,090 --> 00:11:41,210
Come on, boys.

102
00:11:57,808 --> 00:12:01,049
How many did you kill?

103
00:12:04,847 --> 00:12:08,128
We won't talk about it, ok?

104
00:12:08,247 --> 00:12:11,567
You definitely beat more
to death than Didrich.

105
00:12:11,687 --> 00:12:15,288
- You made the fence?
- Yes, yes.

106
00:12:15,407 --> 00:12:18,887
Your hands are well screwed on.

107
00:12:20,846 --> 00:12:24,847
Peter reads books. He goes to school.
He can already read and write.

108
00:12:24,966 --> 00:12:28,446
You will go to Copenhagen
and study one day, perhaps?

109
00:12:28,565 --> 00:12:30,606
Yes, maybe.

110
00:12:30,726 --> 00:12:33,566
We might have a priest in the family.

111
00:12:35,245 --> 00:12:38,245
Hooray! Hooray! Hooray!

112
00:12:38,365 --> 00:12:41,485
Hooray! Hooray! Hooray!

113
00:12:49,164 --> 00:12:53,164
- How many did you whack?
- 120.

114
00:13:11,962 --> 00:13:14,962
How are you?

115
00:13:16,321 --> 00:13:21,322
Could you ensure respect?
So your people look up to you?

116
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:26,360
If you continue
your career in the military?

117
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:38,240
If you had seen what I saw...

118
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:41,639
...I saw grown men
being ripped apart.

119
00:13:41,758 --> 00:13:43,639
Yes.

120
00:13:43,759 --> 00:13:47,879
I stood with my lieutenant...
Then poof...

121
00:13:47,998 --> 00:13:51,599
...his face disappeared.

122
00:13:51,718 --> 00:13:54,678
- It disappeared father.
- Yes, it's war.

123
00:13:54,797 --> 00:13:58,637
Yes, but it could
as well have been me.

124
00:13:58,756 --> 00:14:03,117
War's bloody mess.

125
00:14:08,356 --> 00:14:14,716
You know how it is
to see themselves die every day?

126
00:14:14,835 --> 00:14:17,836
You're alive. If your mother had lived...

127
00:14:17,955 --> 00:14:21,195
she would have been
happy to see you here.

128
00:14:21,314 --> 00:14:24,955
Yes, back in one piece. Healthy.

129
00:14:25,075 --> 00:14:27,715
In one piece.

130
00:14:33,594 --> 00:14:36,714
I am not healthy.

131
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:40,034
Pull yourself together!

132
00:14:43,872 --> 00:14:48,953
Not many could see
Didrich's scar on the soul...

133
00:14:49,072 --> 00:14:53,232
...for who knows what sort of human
hides behind the facade.

134
00:14:57,552 --> 00:15:00,232
Is even the strongest of us...

135
00:15:00,351 --> 00:15:05,712
not sometimes alone in front of the mirror
a weak, sobbing child...

136
00:15:05,831 --> 00:15:09,791
...with strange demons?

137
00:15:13,070 --> 00:15:17,190
Denmark is great.

138
00:15:17,309 --> 00:15:21,510
Large as the largest.

139
00:15:22,909 --> 00:15:27,990
Bigger yet, but the reactionaries...

140
00:15:28,109 --> 00:15:35,550
...conservatives and aristocrats
have the power.

141
00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:37,908
Ditlev?

142
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:42,787
Can't you see that I am working, woman?

143
00:15:44,987 --> 00:15:48,707
Dearest Ditlev,
we have to go to the theater.

144
00:15:48,826 --> 00:15:52,387
Thank you, Emilie. Thank you.

145
00:15:54,146 --> 00:15:57,466
Monrad, It's you, who is the rhetorician.

146
00:15:57,585 --> 00:16:01,426
If we are to expand the Conservatives,
then I must have your help.

147
00:16:01,546 --> 00:16:04,586
Then you must pull yourself together.

148
00:16:04,705 --> 00:16:08,426
- What's up with you?
- Where are you pregnant, Bishop Monrad?

149
00:16:08,545 --> 00:16:12,745
We alone are responsible for collecting
this country together.

150
00:16:12,864 --> 00:16:18,385
Our leader procures instruments.
They play music.

151
00:16:18,504 --> 00:16:22,864
But right now you're as silent
as an empty orchestra pit. Damn, man?

152
00:16:22,983 --> 00:16:28,464
- Then you must speak up in parliament.
- Do not call the devil in my presence.

153
00:16:28,583 --> 00:16:31,984
We have a wonderful project.
Therefore, we call upon all...

154
00:16:32,103 --> 00:16:36,063
...what it takes to close
the mouths of the conservative forces.

155
00:16:36,182 --> 00:16:38,702
Even they love democracy.

156
00:16:38,821 --> 00:16:42,142
Denmark is flag waving
throughout Europe...

157
00:16:42,262 --> 00:16:47,182
...showing that we are a modern,
democratic kingdom for and with the people.

158
00:16:47,301 --> 00:16:51,542
Should we unite as one people
in one collected kingdom, we need...

159
00:16:51,661 --> 00:16:55,101
Their rhetoric, Monrad.
It's the devil in hell...

160
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:59,701
They are so damn good.
They and Grundtvig.

161
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:05,061
Is not God himself,
speaking through priests like you?

162
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:09,700
- Please, Lundbye...
- Well, pull yourself together.

163
00:17:09,819 --> 00:17:12,780
They're the champion.

164
00:17:14,779 --> 00:17:20,220
- What do we have to watch?
- Mrs. Heiberg. "Macbeth".

165
00:17:20,338 --> 00:17:23,738
What thou art promised,
yet do I fear thy nature..

166
00:17:23,858 --> 00:17:27,578
It is too full...

167
00:17:27,697 --> 00:17:33,538
...of the milk o' human kindness.

168
00:17:33,656 --> 00:17:36,697
To catch the nearest way:

169
00:17:36,817 --> 00:17:39,617
Thou wouldst be great;

170
00:17:39,736 --> 00:17:42,696
Art not without ambition,

171
00:17:42,815 --> 00:17:47,376
but without the illness should attend it.

172
00:17:47,495 --> 00:17:51,255
What thou wouldst highly,
that wouldst thou holily;

173
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:57,216
Wouldst not play false,
And yet wouldst wrongly win,

174
00:17:58,814 --> 00:18:04,015
That which cries 'thus thou must do,

175
00:18:04,134 --> 00:18:06,654
if thou have it.

176
00:18:06,773 --> 00:18:12,294
Art thou afeard to be the same
in thine own act and valor...

177
00:18:13,813 --> 00:18:18,614
As thou art in desire.
Wouldst thou have that.

178
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:24,414
Which thou esteem'st the ornament of life.

179
00:18:24,532 --> 00:18:29,092
And live a coward in thine own esteem.

180
00:18:29,211 --> 00:18:33,732
Letting "I dare not" wait upon "I would".

181
00:18:34,771 --> 00:18:38,571
Like the poor cat i' th' adage?
It would have the fish...

182
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:43,291
...but not wet feet.

183
00:18:56,088 --> 00:18:58,729
Bravo.

184
00:19:02,248 --> 00:19:05,449
Bravo.

185
00:19:06,768 --> 00:19:11,888
Because it is your birthday,
you can have this.

186
00:19:14,607 --> 00:19:18,647
- And...
- Save some for Laust.

187
00:19:25,646 --> 00:19:28,286
Thank you, Peter.

188
00:19:32,366 --> 00:19:35,406
- There you go.
- Thank you.

189
00:19:40,005 --> 00:19:46,406
Linnaeus:
"Flora and fauna in Scandinavia".

190
00:19:49,084 --> 00:19:55,085
Yes, it is...
I got it from a Swede.

191
00:19:55,204 --> 00:20:00,244
Yes, it is in Swedish.
Swedish is not that hard to learn.

192
00:20:01,683 --> 00:20:06,803
- I have no books for you, Laust.
- I do not use any.

193
00:20:06,922 --> 00:20:09,003
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

194
00:20:09,123 --> 00:20:13,003
Maybe you can get away with it here.

195
00:20:18,761 --> 00:20:23,521
It should be clean, but look for
the presence of a Prussian at the end.

196
00:20:25,201 --> 00:20:27,161
Come on, Peter.

197
00:20:32,559 --> 00:20:37,360
That day God shone rays of sun
on our world...

198
00:20:37,479 --> 00:20:41,000
...still infinitesimal.

199
00:20:43,039 --> 00:20:48,519
I see only two dirty boys.
And they just look at me...

200
00:20:48,638 --> 00:20:52,399
...as a pillar that rose out of the sea.

201
00:20:52,518 --> 00:20:58,119
But the day must be a day
we will never forget.

202
00:20:59,637 --> 00:21:03,437
It is not a place for girls.
This is our secret place.

203
00:21:03,557 --> 00:21:07,358
- And you have nothing to do here.
- That's right.

204
00:21:07,477 --> 00:21:11,997
You do not have anything to do here
at our place.

205
00:21:13,676 --> 00:21:17,196
Shit heads! Huge...

206
00:21:17,316 --> 00:21:22,477
...filthy fucking shit pig heads!

207
00:21:25,675 --> 00:21:28,715
- Who are you?
- I am Inge.

208
00:21:28,834 --> 00:21:32,155
The new land agent's daughter.

209
00:21:33,634 --> 00:21:38,675
And this place is as much
my place as it is your place.

210
00:21:38,794 --> 00:21:41,634
It's everyone's place.

211
00:21:47,753 --> 00:21:50,633
And what are two such shitheads called?

212
00:21:50,752 --> 00:21:54,113
- Laust.
- We go to school together.

213
00:21:56,232 --> 00:21:59,912
Was it you who was slapped?

214
00:22:02,872 --> 00:22:08,672
What would you do? This guy Egeus has the
kingdom's most beautiful daughter, Hermia...

215
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:11,471
...that all young guys want to marry.

216
00:22:11,591 --> 00:22:14,951
In particular, the two young noble men
Lysander and Demetrius...

217
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:19,551
...and then Egeus forces Hermia
to marry the wrong one...

218
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:23,510
...namely Demetrius,
even though she is loves Lysander.

219
00:22:23,629 --> 00:22:27,510
But the father decides
and he does not like Lysander.

220
00:22:27,629 --> 00:22:33,389
And they tell Hermia,
that she can choose one of three options.

221
00:22:33,509 --> 00:22:39,189
Either marry Demetrius,
enter a monastery or die.

222
00:22:41,427 --> 00:22:44,028
What would you choose then?

223
00:22:46,427 --> 00:22:49,227
What do you choose?

224
00:22:49,347 --> 00:22:52,588
- What to choose?
- What are you doing?

225
00:22:52,707 --> 00:22:55,707
What do you choose then?

226
00:22:57,106 --> 00:23:00,547
Death, of course.

227
00:23:04,905 --> 00:23:08,946
Come on, shit heads. Come on.

228
00:23:09,065 --> 00:23:12,265
It's so nice.

229
00:23:14,505 --> 00:23:16,265
Come on.

230
00:23:16,385 --> 00:23:21,345
Can you blow the clouds back to
where they came from?

231
00:23:24,384 --> 00:23:29,104
And can we not just
remain here forever?

232
00:23:29,223 --> 00:23:33,624
I remember the space,
as if time had stopped completely.

233
00:23:33,743 --> 00:23:37,944
Could we just.. stop time...

234
00:23:38,063 --> 00:23:41,943
...and live forever.

235
00:23:56,101 --> 00:24:01,261
You can stay here a while,
if you really want to.

236
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:07,260
But you know how it is.

237
00:24:12,699 --> 00:24:16,059
You know that the door
should not be locked...

238
00:24:16,179 --> 00:24:19,460
...but you always put the latch on.

239
00:24:19,579 --> 00:24:23,499
If Sebastian were to come home...

240
00:24:25,138 --> 00:24:30,179
...standing there outside
and can not get in...

241
00:24:30,298 --> 00:24:33,898
...while we are sleeping...

242
00:24:34,017 --> 00:24:39,738
and he goes away again.
You know I can't stand the thought.

243
00:24:39,856 --> 00:24:44,057
Mother... Sebastian is not coming home.

244
00:24:44,176 --> 00:24:47,656
