00:48:12,724 --> 00:48:17,124
Denmark! We are Denmark's sons.

492
00:48:17,243 --> 00:48:22,404
And the violence
we see them come up against us...

493
00:48:26,723 --> 00:48:34,404
...stormy, madness in their eyes,
furious with bayonets lowered...

494
00:48:34,522 --> 00:48:41,162
...while they scream "Tod! Tod!"...

495
00:48:41,281 --> 00:48:47,002
...again and again as a living wall,
tumbling up against us. "Tod".

496
00:48:47,121 --> 00:48:52,602
But the Prussians do not know
their ridiculous little war cry...

497
00:48:52,720 --> 00:48:56,360
...is a pure pleasure to listen to
for we Danes...

498
00:48:56,480 --> 00:49:01,161
...because we have painted "Tod"
with blood across the face...

499
00:49:01,279 --> 00:49:07,960
...silent and to tear their
hearts out and eat their guts.

500
00:49:08,079 --> 00:49:13,839
Then I get up lift my sword and scream:

501
00:49:24,277 --> 00:49:28,517
"Then die, fucking German.

502
00:49:28,636 --> 00:49:31,517
Die!"

503
00:49:31,637 --> 00:49:34,837
So I cut myself down among the Prussians...

504
00:49:34,956 --> 00:49:39,517
...and it's raining blood
down over me. And then suddenly...

505
00:49:39,636 --> 00:49:43,076
...suddenly I am alone.

506
00:49:43,195 --> 00:49:49,556
And there are hundreds of
dead Prussians around me.

507
00:50:36,391 --> 00:50:39,311
- Good evening, Inge.
- Good evening.

508
00:50:50,910 --> 00:50:54,350
Did you really kill so many Germans?

509
00:50:54,469 --> 00:50:59,350
- It was nothing.
- I do not understand.

510
00:50:59,469 --> 00:51:02,829
What do not you understand?

511
00:51:05,627 --> 00:51:10,028
Surely it must have been hell for you.

512
00:51:21,786 --> 00:51:25,187
Are you okay?

513
00:51:41,944 --> 00:51:45,624
- Do you like to dance?
- Yes.

514
00:51:45,744 --> 00:51:49,785
- You shall soon go to Copenhagen?
- I think so.

515
00:51:49,904 --> 00:51:55,185
- Then I will come and visit you.
- It might be nice.

516
00:51:55,303 --> 00:51:58,063
And maybe...

517
00:52:01,102 --> 00:52:05,383
...will you home with me afterwards.

518
00:52:15,941 --> 00:52:20,502
There is something special about you, Inge.

519
00:52:20,621 --> 00:52:23,941
I'm just a child.

520
00:52:43,739 --> 00:52:46,699
Can you keep a secret?

521
00:52:46,818 --> 00:52:50,138
I am a frog.

522
00:52:50,257 --> 00:52:53,098
Yes, that's right.

523
00:52:53,218 --> 00:52:55,938
I am a frog.

524
00:52:57,497 --> 00:53:02,498
And if you kiss me,
I might be your prince.

525
00:53:06,336 --> 00:53:09,257
You're drunk.

526
00:53:14,015 --> 00:53:16,376
Quack-Quack.

527
00:53:21,535 --> 00:53:24,296
Where have you been?

528
00:53:26,815 --> 00:53:30,415
Is there something wrong?

529
00:53:30,534 --> 00:53:33,175
Then come.

530
00:53:45,612 --> 00:53:51,253
Condemned German.
Getting into the dungeon.

531
00:53:51,372 --> 00:53:54,532
Peter? Peter?

532
00:54:01,651 --> 00:54:04,372
No, don't shoot.

533
00:54:24,929 --> 00:54:28,530
- It's just something we play.
- Don't die.

534
00:54:28,689 --> 00:54:32,049
I'm watching over you, Peter.

